{"symbol":"Functor.IsCoverDense.iso_of_restrict_iso","info":"CategoryTheory.Functor.IsCoverDense.iso_of_restrict_iso.{v_1, u_1, v_2, u_2, v_4, u_4} {C : Type u_1}
  [Category.{v_1, u_1} C] {D : Type u_2} [Category.{v_2, u_2} D] {K : GrothendieckTopology D} {A : Type u_4}
  [Category.{v_4, u_4} A] {G : C ⥤ D} [G.IsCoverDense K] [G.IsLocallyFull K] {ℱ ℱ' : Sheaf K A} (α : ℱ ⟶ ℱ')
  (i : IsIso (G.op.whiskerLeft α.hom)) : IsIso α
***
Given a locally-full and cover-dense functor `G` and a natural transformation of sheaves
`α : ℱ ⟶ ℱ'`, if the pullback of `α` along `G` is iso, then `α` is also iso.

***
